SIMPLE: defloration
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Defloration
<hw>Def`lo*ra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>defloratio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>d⟦eacute⟧floration</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of deflouring; <as>as, the <ex>defloration</ex>
of a virgin</as>.</def> <rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is chosen as the flower or choicest part;
careful culling or selection.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The laws of Normandy are, in a great measure, the
<qex>defloration</qex> of the English laws.</q> <rj><qau>Sir M.
Hale.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>deflour</ent>⟦br⟧
